# MarketSense — Domain Context

Source: MarketSense product specification and architecture decisions.
Read this before generating any business logic, service, repository, or component file.

---

## WHAT THIS PRODUCT IS

MarketSense is an AI Product Manager intelligence platform for B2B SaaS companies.
Primary users are Product Managers and CPOs at B2B SaaS companies.

The product watches the web for intelligence relevant to PM decisions —
competitor moves, pricing changes, job signals, review patterns, compliance
alerts — and surfaces it as structured, actionable insights with Jira/Linear
integration.

One-line pitch:
"MarketSense doesn't just tell you what's happening in your market — it creates the
work item in Jira, assigns it to the right person, and tracks whether your
response actually worked."

---

## CORE MODULES — MVP

### 1. Competitor Radar (Primary)

Monitors competitor websites for strategic changes across:

- Pricing pages — plan changes, tier additions, limit changes
- Job postings — hiring signals that predict product direction 6-9 months ahead
- Blog / changelog — feature announcements, positioning shifts
- G2 / Capterra reviews — customer pain points in competitor products
- Product Hunt — new entrants before they appear elsewhere
- Features pages — capability additions and removals

### 2. Compliance Radar (Secondary)

Monitors BSE/NSE for regulatory circulars relevant to fintech/regulated verticals.
Extends to any regulated vertical: healthcare, HR tech, legal tech.

