## AGENT MODEL — CRITICAL RULES

- TinyFish agents are MANUAL-FIRST
- Users trigger scans on demand from the dashboard — never automatic by default
- Automation is an opt-in setting, OFF by default in Settings
- Every scan creates a ScanRun record: triggeredBy 'user' | 'automation'
- NEVER write code that auto-triggers agents without explicit user action
- NEVER set automation defaults to enabled

---

## MULTI-TENANCY — CRITICAL RULES

- EVERY database query MUST filter by companyId
- NEVER return data from one company to another company's session
- companyId ALWAYS comes from the authenticated session — NEVER from request body
- Add companyId filter as the FIRST condition in every Prisma where clause
- Every service method that queries data MUST accept and use companyId

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — companyId from session, first in where
const competitors = await db.competitor.findMany({
  where: {
    companyId: session.companyId, // Always first
    isActive: true,
  },
});

// ❌ Wrong — companyId from request body
const { companyId } = await req.json(); // Never do this
```

