## LAYERED SCAN PIPELINE — HOW DATA FLOWS

```
User clicks "Run Scan"
        ↓
POST /api/v1/scan/run
        ↓
scan.service.ts
  → Creates ScanRun (status: running)
  → Fires TinyFish agents in parallel (Promise.allSettled)
        ↓
lib/tinyfish/client.ts
  → run-sse for manual scans
  → run-async for automation mode
        ↓
change-detection.service.ts
  → SHA-256 hash deduplication
  → Compares to previous scan results
  → Creates Change records for new detections
        ↓
enrichment.service.ts
  → Gemini API enriches each Change
  → Assigns signalType, priority, summary
  → Generates recommended actions
        ↓
action.service.ts (if AutomationRule matches)
  → Creates ActionItem
  → Sends to Jira/Linear via Composio
        ↓
ScanRun updated (status: completed | partial | failed)
        ↓
Notification sent to user
```

---

## CHANGE DETECTION RULES

- Hash is SHA-256 of: `title + publishedAt + sourceUrl` (for compliance)
- Hash is SHA-256 of: `planName + price + features` (for pricing)
- NEVER store a Change if its hash already exists for that competitorPageId
- ALWAYS store rawExtracted even if enrichment fails
- ALWAYS store previousExtracted for diffing
- Run enrichment AFTER change detection, not before

---

## GEMINI ENRICHMENT RULES

- Enrichment runs AFTER new Changes are detected and stored
- Enrichment steps run in parallel with Promise.all per Change
- If enrichment fails, Change remains stored with enrichedAt: null
- Never block Change storage waiting for enrichment
- Gemini model: gemini-1.5-pro for enrichment, gemini-1.5-flash for summaries

---

## ACTIONABLE ITEMS — THREE LEVELS

### Level 1 — Suggested (Manual Approval)

MarketSense suggests an action. PM clicks to approve. One-click creation.
UI shows "Create Task" button with pre-filled title, description, priority.

### Level 2 — Draft Queue (Approval Workflow)

MarketSense creates draft tickets in a "MarketSense Inbox" column.
PM reviews, approves, or dismisses. Never auto-sends to external tool.

### Level 3 — Automated (Configured Rules)

PM has set AutomationRules. MarketSense creates tickets automatically when rule matches.
Only available when user has explicitly configured and enabled rules.

